-- Thailand Stocks: Berli, CIMB Thai, Indorama, Krung Thai Bank
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-07-20T09:59:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/thailand-stocks-cimb-thai-indorama-ventures-krung-thai-bank.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Thailand   trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The SET Index fell for a third day, declining 0.4 percent
to 1,208.55. The gauge dropped 0.1 percent this week, the first
decrease in four weeks.  CIMB Thai Bank Pcl (CIMBT)  , a unit of Malaysia’s CIMB
Group Holdings Bhd., declined 2.7 percent to 2.16 baht, the
lowest close since June 21. Profit in the second quarter slumped
89 percent to 28.7 million baht ($905,000).  Indorama Ventures Pcl (IVL)  , the nation’s largest maker
of polyester, rose 1.6 percent to 31 baht, the highest close
since May 15. The company yesterday started commercial
operations of a plant in  Nigeria  to tap demand in Africa, it
said in a regulatory filing today.  Krung Thai Bank Pcl (KTB)  , Thailand’s second-biggest
lender by assets, climbed 1.9 percent to 16.30 baht, halting a
three-day slide. Net income in the second quarter jumped 40
percent to 7.34 billion baht.  Oishi Group Pcl (OISHI TB), controlled by Thailand’s
biggest whiskey and beer producer, dropped 1.2 percent to 160
baht, the steepest loss since June 29. Heineken NV, the world’s
third-biggest brewer, will offer as much as $6 billion to take
over Asia Pacific Breweries Ltd., blocking Thai Beverage Plc
from building its influence in the maker of Tiger beer. Thai
Beverage is the parent of Oishi Group.  Berli Jucker Pcl (BJC)  , an affiliate of Thai Beverage, lost 3.6 percent to 40.5
baht, the most since March 22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
